sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates an Application Load Balancer or a Network Load Balancer.

Inputs:

  • Region - Amazon region.
  • Name - Name of the load balancer.
  • Type - Type of load balancer (Application / Network).
  • Subnet - IDs of public subnets.

Outputs:

  • Load Balancer ARN - ARN of the load balancer.
  • DNS Name - DNS of the load balancer.
  • Canonical Hosted Zone ID - Canonical hosted zone ID of the load balancer.
  • State - State of the load balancer.
  • Created Time - Time when load balancer was created.

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • At least two subnets in two different Availability Zones must be specified.
  • At least one subnet must be specified.
  • InvalidSubnetID.NotFound.

(For information about the errors that are common to all actions, see Common Errors).

To use this action, the corresponding AWS Elastic Load Balancing connection and credential must be created and associated with the AWS Elastic Load Balancing Connection & Credential alias. Learn More
